Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the optimization of the analog transmit waveform for joint delay-Doppler estimation under sub-Nyquist conditions. This involves the use of the Bayesian Cramer-Rao lower bound (BCRLB) and an estimation theoretic design rule for the Fourier coefficients of the analog transmit signal. These concepts are closely related to information theory.
2. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the optimization of the analog transmit waveform for joint delay-Doppler estimation, which involves signal processing techniques such as Fourier analysis and pre-filtering.
3. cs.SP (Speech Processing): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with speech processing, the concepts of signal processing and estimation theory are relevant to this sub-category.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with wireless delay-Doppler channels, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with signal processing and estimation theory, which are relevant to multimedia applications such as audio and video processing.
